icult terrain) unless a creature has a climbing or swimming speed.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'When might a GM require a STR (Athletics) check for climbing or swimming?', 'At their option, they might require a successful check for climbing a slippery vertical surface or one with few handholds, or for gaining any distance in rough water.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How far can you long jump?', 'You can cover a number of feet up to half your walking speed if you move at least 10 feet on foot immediately before the jump.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How far can you standing long jump?', 'You can leap only a quarter of your walking speed.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How much movement does it cost to clear a foot on a long jump?', 'Each foot you clear on the jump costs a foot of movement.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'What is the DC of the STR (Athletics) check to clear a low obstacle on a long jump?', 'DC 10.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'What is the DC of the DEX (Acrobatics) check to land on your feet after a long jump in difficult terrain?', 'DC 10.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How far can you high jump?', 'You can leap into the air a number of feet equal to 3 + your STR modifier if you move at least 10 feet on foot immediately before the jump.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How far can you standing high jump?', 'You can jump only half that distance.']\n['SPECIAL TYPES OF MOVEMENT', 'How much movement does it cost to clear a foot on a high jump?', 'Each foot you clear on the jump costs a foot of movement.\\n1']\n['FALLING', 'What happens when a creature falls from a great height?', 'It lands prone and takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage for every 10 feet it fell, to a maximum of 20d6, unless it has a feature or ability that allows it to avoid taking damage from the fall.']\n['SUFFOCATING', 'How long can a creature hold its breath?', 'A creature can hold its breath for a number of minutes equal to 1 + its CON modifier (minimum of 30 sec