 rules, an action gained from their class or a special feature, or an action that they improvise.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Attack action?', 'With the Attack action, a creature makes one melee or ranged attack. The rules for attacks are detailed in the Making an Attack section.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Cast a Spell action?', 'Spellcasting characters and some monsters can take the Cast a Spell action to cast a spell in combat, but only if the spell has a casting time of 1 action.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Dash action?', 'When a creature takes the Dash action, it gains extra movement for the current turn equal to its speed, after applying any modifiers.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Disengage action?', \"When a creature takes the Disengage action, its movement doesn't provoke opportunity attacks for the rest of the turn.\"]\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Dodge action?', 'When a creature takes the Dodge action, it gains advantage on DEX saves and attack rolls against it have disadvantage if the attacker can see it. This benefit is lost if the creature is incapacitated or its speed drops to 0.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Help action?', 'When a creature takes the Help action, it can aid another creature to complete a task, granting advantage on the next ability check for that task. It can also aid an ally attacking a target within 5 feet, granting advantage on the first attack roll.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Hide action?', 'When a creature takes the Hide action, it makes a DEX (Stealth) check to attempt to hide, following the rules for hiding. If successful, it gains certain benefits, as described in the Unseen Attackers and Targets section.']\n['ACTIONS IN COMBAT', 'What happens when a creature takes the Ready act